File: Details of the programme will be revealed soon. AFP/Luis Robayo JOHANNESBURG - An agreement has been reached between AfriForum and the South African Health Products Regulatory Authority. SAHPRA has agreed to allow the use of Ivermectin topical cream for certain inflammatory skin conditions in adults. READ: Suspected Ivermectin smugglers appear in court AfriForum had taken the regulatory authority to court to force it to register the use of Ivermectin. According to AfriForum, Ivermectin is listed by the World Health Organization as essential medicine and it has been proven safe, even in children.